# Maghz knowledge-domain thesaurus for the kb_english text-search configuration.
#
# Install path: $SHAREDIR/tsearch_data/maghz_thesaurus.ths
#   $SHAREDIR resolves to `pg_config --sharedir` (e.g. /usr/share/postgresql/18).
#   The maghz-pg image (or a routines bootstrap step) must place this file there
#   BEFORE `CREATE TEXT SEARCH DICTIONARY ... (TEMPLATE = thesaurus, ... )` in
#   db/routines.sql resolves it. A missing file fails dictionary creation.
#
# Format (thesaurus template): `phrase : replacement`. The LEFT side is matched against
#   lexemes already normalized by the subdictionary (english_stem, via the Dictionary
#   option in routines.sql), so write phrases in natural SURFACE form — the stemmer
#   normalizes both sides at load and match time, so `nearest neighbor search` also matches
#   `nearest neighbors searches`. Multi-word LEFT is the whole point: it collapses a phrase
#   to one canonical concept lexeme, deduping concepts indexed under different terminology.
#   The RIGHT side is itself passed through the subdictionary; a LEADING `*` on a replacement
#   token bypasses the subdictionary so an opaque/coined token (an acronym, a made-up concept
#   id) is emitted verbatim instead of being stemmed. Opaque RHS tokens below carry the `*`.
#
# Starter rows: a minimal-but-real slice. The full ontology is fleshed out later.

# --- Acronym -> phrase unification (the synonym template cannot do multi-word; thesaurus can) ---
# Both the acronym and its expansion collapse to one opaque canonical lexeme.
machine learning : *ml
artificial intelligence : *ai
natural language processing : *nlp
large language model : *llm
retrieval augmented generation : *rag
continuous integration : *ci
continuous delivery : *cd

# --- Multi-word concept collapse ---
nearest neighbor search : *ann
approximate nearest neighbor : *ann
vector similarity search : *ann
full text search : *fts
inverted index : *fts
knowledge graph : *kg
second brain : *pkm
personal knowledge management : *pkm
spaced repetition : *srs
reciprocal rank fusion : *rrf
hybrid retrieval : *hybridsearch
hybrid search : *hybridsearch
dense retrieval : *densesearch
lexical search : *lexicalsearch
keyword search : *lexicalsearch
